INSERT INTO `article` VALUES (34,'CAREERS','<div class=\"about-tab\">\n<h3 class=\"text-center\">Careers</h3>\n<h3>You</h3>\n<p>Do you like working with team members to drive, lead and execute hands-on initiatives to grow our customer base in a sustainable, repeatable, and affordable fashion. Bring energy in content, sales, technology or creativity to the table?</p>\n<h3>Us</h3>\n<p>We give you an opportunity to help shape a big new service and great team from an early stage and be a part of our growth story.</p>\n<h3>You + Us</h3>\n<p>As a early stage hire, it is an opportunity to grow rapidly which can be achieved using a high level of creativity, ingenuity, and out-of-the-box thinking. If you work well with a team, work hard and enjoy working, please come work with us!</p>\n<p>Email us: <a href=\"mailto:monk@creditmonk.com\"> monk@creditmonk.com</a></p>\n</div>',1,'',1,1),(35,'ABOUT US','<h3 class=\"text-center\">The story about us</h3>\n<div class=\"about-tab\">\n<h3>Need :</h3>\n<p>Doing business but not getting paid. One of the biggest impediments to the $ 1.5 trillion B2B commerce growth in India is the availability of authentic and complete information to allow credit. Most transactions are on clean credit based on very informal sources of references and incomplete or inaccurate information.</p>\n<p>Globally credit is an unsolved issue,for the B2B economy exceeding $15 trillion.</p>\n<h4>Sample India problem numbers</h4>\n<p>India&rsquo;s banking industry : $ 1.23 trillion<br /> Current bad loans (4.6%)&nbsp;&nbsp; : $&nbsp;48 billion ( &gt;100 billion :11% if including stressed loans)</p>\n<h4>India&rsquo;s Private Industry</h4>\n<p>Bad Debt as % of net profit : 10-15%&nbsp;<br />Delayed Payments :&nbsp;Minimum 50% of sales</p>\n<p>A small retailer with sales of Rs. 1 crore/year will be loosing minimum Rs. 50,000 annually as bad debts. Additionally the time and interest loss in delayed payments.</p>\n<h3>Us :</h3>\n<p><strong>Monk: </strong>Studied in India and Technology in England. Worked stacking shelves, in a call center, tech and a good amount of time in the B2B space. That should have been progression right? Wrong, because you might work you&rsquo;re a#$ off, but in India, do you get paid?</p>\n<p>After having heard excuses like &ldquo;Checks not signed as they lost their pens in the mines&rdquo; and &ldquo;electricity had gone so they could not see how to sign&rdquo; I considered it easier to go back to stacking shelves.</p>\n<p><strong>Enter Big Monk: </strong>Working in the B2B space for many years, a key issue was the absolute helplessness of business owners in getting their payments on time. Having worked with large-scale industries, the issue was huge and lowered his profit margin way more than it should. At times, it felt like he was a private bank for customers.</p>\n<p>Seeing Poor companies and Rich Owners eat into his peace, and after trying multiple things and absolutely failing, he thought he wanted to stop reviewing food and hotels, instead focus on his bread and butter, which pay for those.</p>\n<h3>Solution :</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.esolz.co.in/lab4/credit_monk/home/\">CreditMonk.com</a>: </strong> We seek to make credit a good word!</p>\n<p><strong>Team CreditMonk: </strong> A small but super dedicated team of tech and support moderators who love the fact that they will make it way easier for people to do business. And a bigger team of shared resources to ensure we have access to the best support, advice and scalability that we have no doubt we will soon need.</p>\n</div>',1,'',1,0),(36,'HOW IT WORKS','<h3>MEET</h3>\n<h4>Distributor A</h4>\n<p>Mr. Distributor has been in the business for 35 years and as competition has increased and margins reduced, payment delays have become too expensive to his bottom line. He is tired of credit issues and needs to keep calling up for references in the business to understand a customers market reputation and credit worthiness. Considering he gets most of his information from competitors, it might not always be reliable. He has developed high blood pressure in the last 5 years due to uncontrolled credit. Many of his valued customers have a good payment habit but those who don&rsquo;t cause the bottom line to plunge.</p>\n<h4>Manufacturer A</h4>\n<p>Ms. Manufacturer has been manufacturing engineering products for 10 years and does not get paid for even 120 days by some customers. Her customers take product on credit, don&rsquo;t pay when due, and if she refuses to supply until paid, they buy from her competitor who sells not knowing the payment issues he will also have to deal with. Legal recourse has yielded no benefit and proven to be time consuming and expensive. Bad debts are increasing year on year and causing her to believe its better to shut shop and leave this business.</p>\n<h4>Professional A</h4>\n<p>Mr. Lawyer is a Lawyer spending many late nights completing urgent client work. In spite of 18-hour workdays, clients don&rsquo;t pay and there is no time to keep calling and following up for payments. Many of his clients pay on time but those who don&rsquo;t, add a high bad debt burden, which means precious time wasted.</p>\n<h3>Enter creditmonk</h3>\n<p>They all sign up on creditmonk and decide to put up their reviews so that other people dealing with their debtors know the real picture about the payment issues &ndash; Good And Bad.</p>\n<h3>Reviews</h3>\n<div class=\"privacy-sub\">\n<p>1. For the good paymasters they put up positive reviews for their good business practices and ethics.</p>\n<p>2. For the bad paymasters they rate and review them negatively.</p>\n</div>\n<h3>Benefits</h3>\n<div class=\"privacy-sub\">\n<p>1. Good companies get rated higher and get better credit terms and serve as a positive example to the market</p>\n<p>2. Debtors delaying payment get motivated to improve their payment habit</p>\n<p>3. Management notices what they might not be aware of</p>\n<p>4. Companies who have a &ldquo;Do a case, we don&rsquo;t care&rdquo; -Bully companies due to concern of public shaming start taking notice of their payment habit</p>\n</div>\n<h3>The also discover the benefit for company owners to:</h3>\n<div class=\"privacy-sub\">\n<p>1. Claim their profile and add/amend information</p>\n<p>2. Reply to reviews and comments about their companies</p>\n<p>3. Review other companies they transact with</p>\n<p>4. Invite their suppliers/people they work with to review their company</p>\n</div>\n<h3>Good Karma</h3>\n<p>We all make Credit a good word! <a href=\"[BASE]\"> Sign up</a> its FREE</p>\n<p>Further details in <a href=\"[BASE]home/helpCenter?tab=Guiding\">Guidelines</a></p>',1,'',1,1),(37,'PRIVACY POLICY','<p>At the outset, please note that at www.creditmonk.com we are committed towards protecting your privacy. We understand and appreciate that providing information online involves a great deal of trust on your part. We value your confidence in us and treat the same on a high priority so as to ensure the confidentiality of the personal information you provide to us. We would use the information we collect in order to provide a more personalized experience for business transactions. The following policy indicates the manner in which the information collected by us would be treated and our practices and procedures towards protection of your privacy.</p>\n<p>This Policy inter-alia specifies the kind of information that we may collect from you when you access or use our websites, applications and other online services (collectively, our&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;Services&rdquo;</strong> ) and our practices for collecting, using, maintaining, protecting and disclosing the aforesaid information.</p>\n<p>This Policy inter-alia specifies the kind of information that we may collect from you when you access or use our websites, applications and other online services (collectively, our&nbsp;&ldquo;Services&rdquo;) and our practices for collecting, using, maintaining, protecting and disclosing the aforesaid information.</p>\n<p>Please read this Policy carefully to understand our policies and practices before submitting your personal information to us. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, your choice is not to use our Services. By accessing or using our Services, you unconditionally and irrevocably agree to this Policy. This Policy may be updated / modified / changed from time to time and you are deemed to accept the same through your continued use of our Services, therefore we request you to check the Policy from time to time for updates. If you have any questions about this Policy, you may email us at support@creditmonk.com.</p>\n<p>This Policy is in addition to the www.creditmonk.com <a href=\"[BASE]home/disclaimer\">Disclaimer</a> and <a href=\"[BASE]home/termsCondition\"> Terms and Conditions </a> (the &ldquo; <strong><a href=\"[BASE]home/termsCondition\"> Terms and Conditions</a> </strong>&rdquo;) and must be read together with the same.</p>\n<h6>1. INFORMATION WHICH WE COLLECT</h6>\n<div class=\"privacy-sub\">\n<h4>1.1. How we collect the information</h4>\n<p>1.1.1. We collect several kinds of information from and about users of our Services, including information about the nature of credit re-paying capacity of individuals, corporates, firms, limited liability partnerships, etc. (&ldquo;Organisation/s&rdquo;), their payment / repayment habits, credit terms and conditions offered to them, the industry standards, relevant details of the Organisations like their name, address, offices, key personnel, turnover, market share, etc. and other matters incidental or ancillary thereto.</p>\n<p>1.1.2. We collect this information directly from you when you provide it to us, and/or automatically as you navigate through our Services (information collected automatically may include usage details, IP addresses and information collected through cookies, web beacons and other tracking technologies).</p>\n<p>1.1.3. The website is optimized for registered users. By registering, you can obtain benefits such as the opportunity to write reviews / posts and further personalize your experience. If you choose not to register, you can still use some portions of the site. In that case, we may track your IP addresses and analyze which URLs you have come from and visited.</p>\n<p>1.2. Information provided by you: &nbsp;The information we collect on or through our Services may include:</p>\n<p>1.2.1. Your full name, email address, postal code, password and other information you may provide with your account, such as your gender, mobile phone number and website. You may optionally provide us with this information through third-party sign-in services such as Facebook and Google Plus if you choose to log in through any of such portals. In such cases, we obtain and store whatever information is made available to us by you through these sign-in services.</p>\n<p>1.2.2. Information and/or reviews you provide on our website, comments in the nature of seconding some other user&rsquo;s reviews.</p>\n<p>1.2.3. If the Users so desire, the anonymity can be maintained before or at the time of posting the reviews on the website.</p>\n<p>1.2.4. How long you used our Services and which features you used.</p>\n<p>1.2.4. How long you used our Services and which features you used.</p>\n<p>1.2.5. The advertisements you clicked on our website.</p>\n<p>1.2.6. If the Users wish to communicate with other Users / Organisations and /or make any complaint to the management and/or support team, the same shall be sent to the grievous centre or such e-mail /or Helpline numbers so provided in the website.</p>\n<p>1.2.7. If you post reviews or otherwise use our Services in any manner, we may collect and store information about you to process your requests and automatically complete forms for future transactions, including (but not limited to) your phone number, address, email, etc. This information may be shared with third-parties which 