n the social media service. Your interactions with social media companies are governed by their privacy policies.</p>\n<p>3.1.7. To enforce or apply our Terms of Conditions and other agreements, including for billing and collection purposes. 6</p>\n<p>3.1.8. If we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect the rights, property, or safety of the website, our customers or others. This includes exchanging information with other companies and organizations for the purposes of fraud protection and credit risk reduction.</p>\n<p>3.1.8. If we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect the rights, property, or safety of the website, our customers or others. This includes exchanging information with other companies and organizations for the purposes of fraud protection and credit risk reduction.</p>\n<p>3.1.9. We may share your information in any other circumstances where we have your consent.</p>\n<p>3.2. Payment Information</p>\n<p>To use our premium based services, the users can make payments online through the payment mechanism and if there is any difficulty in making the payments, the same can be resolved by and in way of contacting our support team. By submitting your credit or debit card account information through our Services, you expressly consent to the sharing of your information with our server, third-party payment processors, and other third-party service providers (including but not limited to vendors who provide fraud detection services to us and other third parties), and you further agree that when you use a credit or debit card to secure a reservation through our Sites, we provide your credit or debit card account information (including card number and expiration date) to our third- party payment service providers; and when you initially provide your credit or debit card account information through our Services in order to use our services, we provide your credit or debit card account information to our third-party payment service providers. As explained in our Terms and Conditions, these third parties may store your credit or debit card account information so you can use our payment services through our Services in the future.</p>\n<h4>4. REVIEWS POSTED BY USERS</h4>\n<p>4.1. Information submitted by Users as part of a review is automatically displayed on the site (so long as it passes the software filters). We may use the review or teaser portions thereof throughout the site. Subject to the limitations discussed in this Policy and the Terms and Conditions, you can change a review within 30 days of posting using the tools provided by the website. If you wish to delete a review, you may do so in your User Profile &ndash; Reviews section within 30 days of adding your review. Or email on support@creditmonk.com. Your request may or may not be granted, depending on the reason of your request. In all cases, we will make best efforts to protect your privacy, as laid down in this Policy.</p>\n<p>4.2. One of the key aspects of the website is that it permits users to provide their opinions / reviews regarding payment habits, etc. of Organisations. The system assesses your prior experiences on the site (as evidenced by how you\'ve rated other reviews or trusted/distrusted other members / Organisations), and then uses these experiences to dynamically sort the database of Organisations for you based on those that are more likely to interest you. To do this, we capture information about your interactions with other users and then processes this information. The more you interact with others, the more personalized your subsequent uses of the site will be.</p>\n<p>4.3. Your reviews might be removed if they flag off certain filters in our system, are flagged off by users as suspicious/for other reasons and/or you posted a review for the same companies more than once within 30 days. In this case, your latest review is considered valid and displayed.</p>\n<p>4.4. Your review might also be deleted for other